  <li><em>Reframe</em>: Donâ€™t let the perfect be the enemy of the good. To borrow a phrase from a old colleague, you can get a lot done by just drilling little holes into the decaying IT edifice. Think more about <a href="https://medium.comsmall-city-pieces-loosely-joined-5202fb5a93e3">small pieces loosely joined</a>, not big integrations atop shoddy foundations.</li>
